## Nutrition Protocols (70kg)

**Fuel sources:**
- Gels: Roctane Ultra Endurance (sea salt chocolate) — ~25g carbs (maltodextrin/glucose), 35mg caffeine, 125mg sodium per gel. Test sea salt chocolate in training — if cloying at high HR, switch to lemonade or pineapple for race day
- Drink mix: carb drink with fructose (Maurten 320, SiS Beta Fuel, or Precision Fuel PF 90) — provides the fructose side for dual-transport absorption
- Electrolyte caps: SaltStick Caps — 1 cap delivers ~215mg sodium, ~63mg potassium, ~22mg magnesium

**Why dual-transport at 60-65g/hr:** gut absorbs max ~60g/hr glucose via SGLT1. Adding fructose (separate GLUT5 transporter) allows higher totals without GI distress. At OCR intensity blood is constantly shunted from the gut to working muscles (grip, carries, climbs), so 60-65g/hr is the maximum absorption zone for a 70kg athlete — higher intake risks the "gut brick" during obstacles like sandbag carries and the Dunk Wall

**Vest configuration (Kiprun 5L/10L):**
- Flask 1 (500ml): Maurten 320 or Beta Fuel, full strength (80g carbs) — "Engine Oil"
- Flask 2 (500ml): plain water — "Neutralizer" for gels and salt caps only
- Rear bladder (1.0-1.5L): plain water for general thirst
- **Sip-Sip-Gulp rule:** Sip Flask 1 (carb mix) every 10-15 min. Sip bladder (water) whenever thirsty. Gulp Flask 2 (water) only to chase Roctane gels and SaltStick caps

**Protocol A — Pre + After** (sessions 75-95 min, moderate-high intensity)
- Before (90-120 min pre): 40-50g HBCDs in 500ml water
- After: 1 electrolyte cap + 5g L-glutamine in water

**Protocol B — Pre + During + After** (HIIT 75+ min, long runs 90-120 min)
- Before (90-120 min pre): 40-50g HBCDs in 500ml water + 2-3 rice cakes with Nutella, OR + ~50-60g cream of rice dry weight. On race rehearsal mornings avoid Nutella/fats — fats delay gastric emptying
- During: 1 Roctane gel midway chased with 150ml plain water + sip carb drink mix throughout — aim for 50-60g carbs/hr
- Electrolytes: 1 cap per 45-60 min chased with 100ml plain water
- After: 1 electrolyte cap + 5g L-glutamine in water

**Protocol C — Pre + During + After** (long runs 120+ min, OCR simulations, race rehearsals)
- Before (90-120 min pre): 50-60g HBCDs in 500ml water + ~100g cream of rice dry weight with banana + honey (no Nutella — fats delay gastric emptying)
- During — follow the hourly cycle:
  - 0:00-0:30: sip ~170ml Flask 1 (carb mix)
  - 0:30: 1 SaltStick cap + gulp Flask 2 (plain water)
  - 0:45: 1 Roctane gel + gulp Flask 2 (plain water)
  - Aim for 60-65g carbs/hr (~27g drink + 25g gel)
- Take gels on uphills (steady HR), not fast downhills (bouncing causes GI distress)
- After: 1 electrolyte cap + 5g L-glutamine in water + 20g whey or BCAAs

**Race Day Protocol** (sub-3-hour effort)
- Before (3-4 hours pre): 1.5-2g/kg = ~120-140g carbs — 100g cream of rice (dry weight) + 1 banana + 1 tbsp honey/maple syrup. No Nutella, no fats — fats delay gastric emptying
- 30 min pre: 1 Roctane gel + 200ml plain water
- During — the "65g Performance" hourly cycle (repeat 3x):
  - 0:00-0:30: sip ~170ml Flask 1 (carb mix)
  - 0:30: 1 SaltStick cap + gulp Flask 2 (plain water)
  - 0:45: 1 Roctane gel + gulp Flask 2 (plain water)
  - Total per hour: ~27g (drink) + 25g (gel) = 52-65g carbs depending on sip size
- Take gels on uphills (steady HR), not fast downhills (bouncing causes GI distress)
- Crisis management:
  - Cramp: 1 SaltStick cap + 200ml plain water immediately (not carb mix — it slows salt absorption)
  - Gut rot/nausea: stop gels, sip plain water only for 15 min to let stomach clear
- Caffeine total: ~140mg (4 gels including pre-race) — safe ceiling for 70kg to avoid HR jitter on Spear Throw
- Sodium total: ~550mg/hr — verified for 70kg at 20°C
- After: 1-2 electrolyte caps + 5g L-glutamine + 20g whey or BCAAs


